{"id": "duc04-testb-4:1#5", "contents": "Hariri has been instrumental in rebuilding Lebanon's economy and infrastructure after the civil war. He has created a multibillion-dollar program to rebuild the country and has stabilized the currency, restoring confidence in the postwar economy. However, his government has been dogged by accusations of corruption. Despite this, Hariri has remained in office as caretaker prime minister since Lahoud's inauguration on Tuesday. Lahoud has pledged to clean up the corruption-plagued administration, but it remains to be seen how this will affect Hariri's chances of securing a fourth term."}
